



Sir
Camp at Cambridge October 24th 1775



Your Favour of the 12th Instant I duly received, and thank you for inclosing Captain Thompsons Information. The Contents of the Deposition, now transmitted to you, are of such a
[232]
Nature, that I thought, no Time should be lost in giving you the earliest Notice of them.1 I am Sir yr mo. obt Servt

Go. W.

